Class Object2DoubleFunctions.Singleton<K>

  • java.lang.Object
    • it.unimi.dsi.fastutil.objects.AbstractObject2DoubleFunction<K>
      • it.unimi.dsi.fastutil.objects.Object2DoubleFunctions.Singleton<K>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Function<K,java.lang.Double>, Object2DoubleFunction<K>, java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    Object2DoubleMaps.Singleton
    Enclosing class:
    Object2DoubleFunctions

    public static class Object2DoubleFunctions.Singleton<K>
extends AbstractObject2DoubleFunction<K>
implements java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable
    An immutable class representing a type-specific singleton function. Note that the default return value is still settable.

    Note that albeit the function is immutable, its default return value may be changed.

    This class may be useful to implement your own in case you subclass a type-specific function.
